<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-124-288 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 943 538</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 24 1991 v5 n18 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Drafix CAD offers users drafting under Windows. (ForesightResources Corp's computer-aided design software runs underMicrosoft Windows 3.0)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stone, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The $695 Drafix CAD for Windows 3.0 software package fromForesight Resources Corp (Kansas City, MO) is a CAD program thatoffers numerous graphics capabilities while complying closely tothe Windows interface standards.andP;  The object-oriented CAD packagerepresents drawings as a set of objects each defined by a set ofattributes, with a alphanumeric text and graphic informationstored in a data base.andP;  Other functional capabilities includelayered drawings, 'power drawing,' multiple simultaneousinteractive viewpoints, associative dimensioning, symbol librariesand varied text formats and fonts.andP;  The software requires aminimum of an Intel 80386-based IBM PC-compatible microcomputerthat can run Windows 3.0.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Foresight Resources Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Drafix Windows CAD (CAD software) (Design and construction).andO;Topic:     Computer-Aided DesignGraphics SoftwareSystem DesignFunctional CapabilitiesObject-Oriented Programming.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>